  <item>
    <title>DIRECTOR OF VSL VENTURE SDN BHD WAS CHARGED UNDER SECTION 364(2), COMPANIES ACT 1965 FOR ALLEGEDLY MAKING A FALSE STATEMENT TO THE REGISTRAR</title>
    <link>http://www.ssm.com.my/en/press-release/director-vsl-venture-sdn-bhd-was-charged-under-section-3642-companies-act-1965</link>
    <description>&lt;div class=&quot;field field-name-body field-type-text-with-summary field-label-hidden&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-items&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;field-item even&quot; property=&quot;content:encoded&quot;&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Monday, 4th April 2016: A director of VSL Venture Sdn Bhd (712541-P) (‘VSLV’), Lim Piang Soon, was charged for an offence under Section 364(2) of the Companies Act 1965 (‘CA 1965’) at Ipoh Sessions Court on 31.3.2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Lim Piang Soon was charged for making a false statement through the lodgment of Form 49 in relation to the resignation of Wong Kia Tung as a director of VSLV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Section 364(2) of the CA 1965 provides for punishment of 10 years imprisonment or fine of RM250, 000 or both upon conviction.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Tuan Murtazadi Bin Amran, the Sessions Court Judge ordered Lim Piang Soon to be released on RM15, 000 bail with one surety and his international passport be impounded by the court. The case was fixed for a mention on 3rd of May 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;The SSM senior prosecution officer, Faizal Mahdi Mahmud appeared for the prosecution meanwhile Lim Piang Soon was represented by counsel, Andrew Soong Tze Toong.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;SURUHANJAYA SYARIKAT MALAYSIA&lt;br /&gt;4th APRIL 2016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;hr /&gt;&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;PENGARAH VSL VENTURE SDN BHD DIDAKWA MENGIKUT SEKSYEN 364(2) AKTA SYARIKAT 1965 KERANA MEMBUAT PENYATAAN PALSU KEPADA PENDAFTAR SYARIKAT (‘SSM’)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Isnin, 4 April 2016: Seorang pengarah syarikat VSL Venture Sdn Bhd (712541-P) (‘VSLV’), Lim Piang Soon, 46 tahun, didakwa di Mahkamah Sesyen Ipoh pada 31.3.2016 kerana dikatakan telah melakukan kesalahan di bawah seksyen 364(2) Akta Syarikat 1965 (‘AS 1965’).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Pertuduhan yang dikenakan terhadap Lim Piang Soon adalah berkaitan dengan perbuatan membuat penyataan palsu kepada Pendaftar Syarikat (‘SSM’) melalui serahsimpan Borang 49, iaitu berkenaan peletakan jawatan Wong Kia Tung, sebagai pengarah VSLV.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Kesalahan di bawah seksyen 364(2) AS 1965 memperuntukkan hukuman penjara sehingga tempoh 10 tahun atau denda sehingga RM250,000 atau kedua-duanya sekali jika sabit kesalahan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Hakim Tuan Murtazadi Bin Amran memerintahkan Lim Piang Soon diikat jamin RM15,000 dengan seorang penjamin dan pasport antarabangsanya diserahkan kepada Mahkamah. Kes akan disebut semula pada 3 Mei 2016.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;Pendakwaan kes dikendalikan oleh Faizal Mahdi Mahmud, Pegawai Pendakwa Kanan SSM dari ibu pejabat manakala Lim Piang Soon diwakili peguam Encik Andrew Soong Tze Toong.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style=&quot;text-align: justify;&quot;&gt;SURUHANJAYA SYARIKAT MALAYSIA&lt;br /&gt;4 APRIL 2016&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
